}}{{TIDTOC|adapter}} ==Overview== [http://web.archive.org/web/20000621171902/http://catalog.belkin.com/IWCatSectionView.process?IWAction=Load&Merchant_Id=1&Section_Id=35 Visible on the '''Belkin''' Catalog 07/2000] (which is also the first available USB Hub catalog page on archive.org)
"F5U007" and "Rev:2.1" is silkscreened on the board of a F5U007-UNV unit (the S/N appears to be 0147). :This particular hub uses four '''Canicon''' branded radial capacitors and two double-stacked '''ACON''' Female A USB connectors. :The Male A cable is attached to the board via a 5-pin header.
The power adapter included with the hub would appear to be a '''L.S.E.''' LSE9801B05 (USA) (100-125VAC ~ 50/60Hz, 0.6A -> 5VDC 3A).
